    <p>1 CRIS­TIANO RON­ALDO V LIONEL MESSI FOOT­BALL</p>
    <p>One rises, the other stays low to the ground. One is colour­ful, the other quiet. To­gether they have won 11 Bal­lon d’Ors, nine Cham­pi­ons League ti­tles and three Best Fifa Men’s Player awards. And they are not fin­ished yet.</p>
    <p>2 LIN DAN V LEE CHONG WEI BAD­MINTON</p>
    <p>The Chi­nese and the Malaysian met five times at the All Eng­land, twice at the world cham­pi­onships, and thrice at the Olympics. When Lee re­tired, Lin, who led 28-12 in past meet­ings, said: “I will be alone on the court and no one will ac­com­pany me.”</p>
    <p>3 RAFAEL NADAL V ROGER FED­ERER TEN­NIS</p>
    <p>Left hand ver­sus right, bull ver­sus mata­dor, Spain v Switzer­land. They played 40 matches (Nadal 24-16) over 15 years and 14 times at the Grand Slams. A book, Strokes Of Ge­nius, was writ­ten on their 2008 Wim­ble­don fi­nal and also a doc­u­men­tary made.</p>

